Clerq — Open-Source Local MCS
============================

Attribution: OpenClerq was inspired by OpenClaw
(https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw) in its approach to gateway,
skills, and local-first agent orchestration. Our implementation is original.

- The open-source Clerq software is provided AS IS. Use at your own risk.
- No warranty, no responsibility. Developers run it on their local machine,
  with their own API keys, and may build and use any modules they want.
- Clerq also offers (or will offer) a hosted service (accounts, subscriptions,
  modules with built-in skills on our servers with our API keys). Implementation
  and terms for that service are separate from this repo.

